
		    SICStus Prolog binary distribution
		===========================================

Prerequisites:
  You need to have perl installed and available in your PATH. Perl can
  be obtained (for free) from http://www.cpan.org/

To install SICStus Prolog, type

% ./InstallSICStus

and follow the instructions on the screen. When installation is complete,
you can access the documentation locally by opening

	      file:/<install-dir>/lib/sicstus-<ver>/doc/html/

Where <install-dir> is the installation directory you specified during
installation and <ver> is the SICStus version (e.g. 4.3.0).

For further information, updates, patches, and online documentation, please
visit the SICStus Prolog website at

			http://www.sics.se/sicstus/

Report bugs etc. using

	    http://www.sics.se/sicstus/bugreport/bugreport.html
      
/SICStus Support
